<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Darwin Dashboard — LinkedIn CAPI Health</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <main class="container">
    <header class="landing-header">
      <h1>Darwin Dashboard</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">LinkedIn CAPI integration health, conversion coverage &amp; recommendations</p>
    </header>

    <section class="card search-card">
      <h2>Look up an advertiser</h2>
      <p class="muted">Enter a LinkedIn ad account ID or sponsored account URN to load the CAPI health dashboard for that advertiser.</p>

      <% if (error) { %>
        <p class="search-error"><%= error %></p>
      <% } %>

      <form method="get" action="/dashboard" class="search-form">
        <label class="search-label" for="accountId">Account ID or URN</label>
        <div class="search-row">
          <input
            id="accountId"
            type="text"
            name="accountId"
            value="<%= prefill %>"
            placeholder="508833998  or  urn:li:sponsoredAccount:508833998"
            autocomplete="off"
            spellcheck="false"
            required
            class="search-input"
          />
          <button type="submit" class="btn-search">Load dashboard →</button>
        </div>
      </form>

      <p class="search-hint muted">
        Demo mode: enter <strong>508833998</strong> to preview with sample data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card how-card">
      <h2>What this dashboard shows</h2>
      <ul class="how-list">
        <li><strong>Health score</strong> — overall CAPI integration quality based on event volume, match quality, and deduplication.</li>
        <li><strong>30-day trend</strong> — event volume and match quality over the last 30 days.</li>
        <li><strong>Conversions</strong> — every conversion rule in the account, its type, enabled status, and whether it is linked to active campaigns.</li>
        <li><strong>Signal breakdown</strong> — per-field match rates for <code>lifatid</code>, <code>sha256email</code>, <code>ligiantid</code>, <code>axiomid</code>, <code>oracleid</code>, and people match info.</li>
        <li><strong>Recommendations</strong> — prioritised, actionable suggestions to improve match quality and coverage.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
